<h2>Appearance</h2>
<h4><span style="font-weight: bold;">Design and Formats</span><span style="font-weight: bold;"></span></h4>
<ul style="font-weight: normal;"><li><span style="font-weight: bold;">Color scheme</span>.You may choose between <samp>black</samp>, <samp>dark grey</samp>, <samp>grey</samp>, <samp>white</samp> and <samp>platform</samp>. Text
colors are adapted automatically. "Platform" is the default color
scheme of the operating system.&nbsp;<br>Additional color schemes can &nbsp;be added by placing <a href="css.html">CSS style sheets</a> into the <code>dropins/</code> subfolder of the installation directory.</li>
  <li><span style="font-weight: bold;">Units</span>. Here you can set
the units for distances and dimensions. The unit for distances affects
the proximity search. The unit for dimensions affects the display and
search for the physical size of an image, the specifications for
exhibitions, and the layout settings for Print and PDF.<br>
  </li>
</ul>
<h4><span style="font-weight: bold;">Thumbnails</span><span style="font-weight: bold;"></span></h4>
<ul style="font-weight: normal;">
  
  
  <li><span style="font-weight: bold;">Thumbnail labels</span>. By
default, the image title and additional information is shown in the
thumbnail label. However, the title may completely be switched off or
configured using a template.<br>
Templates are constructed from constant text parts
and variables. You can type in both, but it is much more comfortable
and safe to select the variables from a list by clicking the button <abbr>Insert variable..</abbr>. or <abbr>Insert metadata...</abbr><abbr></abbr>. The later refers to the different fields defined with an image such as EXIF and IPTC data.<br>
    <br>
When a variable or metadata cannot be resolved (e.g. a field is
undefined) the variable is simply deleted from the template. This is
sometimes not sufficient: you may want to delete some extra text with
it. For this purpose a special syntax is provided:<br>
    <br>
    <table style="text-align: left; width: 100%;" border="1" cellpadding="2" cellspacing="2">
      <tbody>
        <tr>
          <td style="vertical-align: top; font-weight: bold;">Pattern<br>
          </td>
          <td style="vertical-align: top; font-weight: bold;">Description</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td style="vertical-align: top;"><code>(?...?)<br>
          </code></td>
          <td style="vertical-align: top;"><span style="font-weight: bold;">Conditional group type 1</span><br>The complete expression between the parantheses will be deleted if <span style="font-weight: bold;">all</span> variables and subgroups within the paranthesis remain unresolved. <br>
          <span style="font-weight: bold;">Example:</span><code><br>
 (?Shot in </code><code>{meta=iptc_location_created&amp;city}?)</code></td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td style="vertical-align: top;"><code>(??...?)</code></td>
          <td style="vertical-align: top;"><span style="font-weight: bold;">Conditional group type 2<br>
          </span>The complete expression between the parantheses will be deleted if at least <span style="font-weight: bold;">one</span> variable or subgroup within the paranthesis remains unresolved.<br>
          <span style="font-weight: bold;">Example:</span><br>
(??<code>{meta=owner},</code><code> {</code><code>yyyy</code><code>}?</code><code>)</code></td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td style="vertical-align: top;"><code>...|(...)<br>
          </code></td>
          <td style="vertical-align: top;"><span style="font-weight: bold;">Fallback</span><br>
If the expression (variable, conditional group, or another fallback) in front of the<code> | </code>is unresolved, the expression within the parantheses is used instead. Otherwise it is discarded, <br>
          <span style="font-weight: bold;">Example:<br>
          </span><code> {meta=iptc_location_created&amp;city}|(</code><code>{title})</code><br>
          </td>
        </tr>
      </tbody>
    </table>
    <br>Conditional groups and fallbacks can be nested.<br>

This mark-up is finally removed from the template when the hover text is generated.<br>
    <br>
<span style="font-weight: bold;"></span></li>


  <li><span style="font-weight: bold;">Decoration</span><br>
  </li>
<ul style="font-weight: normal;">
    
    <li><span style="font-weight: bold;">Show status mark.</span>
Check this option to display a green status mark for images with status
"Ready for publishing" or RAW images with status "Corrected".</li>
    <li><span style="font-weight: bold;">Max. number of displayed regions.</span> Limits the number of&nbsp;regions (face, pet, focus, barcode) shown in a thumbnail.</li>
    <li><span style="font-weight: bold;">Show location pin</span>. The location pin informs about the presence of location data and allows access to the map view with a single click.</li>
    <li><span style="font-weight: bold;">Show color code in thumbnails.</span> Select an option to display color codes in&nbsp;thumbnails:</li>
<ul>
      
      
      
      
      
      <li><span style="font-weight: bold;">No</span>. No colorcodes will be shown in thumbnails</li>
      <li><span style="font-weight: bold;">Automatic</span>. Color codes are automatically determined by the rules defined in the <span style="font-style: italic;">Automatic Color Coding</span> box (see below). Manually set color codes override the automatic codes.</li>
      <li><span style="font-weight: bold;">Manual</span>. Only manually set color codes are shown.</li>

      
      </ul>
    <li><span style="font-weight: bold;">Show rating in thumbnails.</span>
Select&nbsp;<samp>by size</samp> to show the rating as one differently sized star. Select&nbsp;<samp>by count</samp> to show the rating as a variable number of stars.</li>
    <li><span style="font-weight: bold;">Show rotate buttons in thumbnails.</span> Check this option to display the rotate buttons at the bottom of the thumbnail.</li>
    <li><span style="font-weight: bold;">Show voicenote button in thumbnails.</span> Check this option to display the&nbsp;voicenote button at the bottom of the thumbnail.</li>
    <li><span style="font-weight: bold;">Show Expand/Collapse button in thumbnails</span>.
Check this option to display the <abbr>+</abbr> or <abbr>-</abbr>&nbsp;
buttons at the top of the thumbnail
for controlling the expanded/collapsed state of the thumbnail.
Collapsed means that subsequent images with the same name are shown as
one thumbnail.</li>
</ul>
</ul>
<h4>Color codes</h4>
<span style="font-weight: bold;"></span><ul style="font-weight: normal;"><li><span style="font-weight: bold;">Show color code in thumbnails.</span> Select an option to display color codes in&nbsp;thumbnails:</li><ul style="font-weight: normal;"><li><span style="font-weight: bold;">no</span>. No colorcodes will be shown in thumbnails</li><li><span style="font-weight: bold;">automatic</span>. Color codes are automatically determined by the rules defined in the <span style="font-style: italic;">Automatic Color Coding</span> box (see below). Manually set color codes override the automatic codes.</li><li><span style="font-weight: bold;">user defined.</span> Only manually set color codes are shown.</li></ul><li><span style="font-weight: bold;">Automatic Color Coding</span>. This group is only shown if the automatic color code option was chosen. <br>For each color code you may specify a <span style="font-weight: bold;">criterion</span> selecting the images for which the color code is to be shown (similar to specifying a <a href="collectionEdit.html">collection criterion</a>).<br><br><span style="font-weight: bold;">Note: </span>Automatic
color coding does not modify the meta data of images but only
influences the display of color codes in the user interface. The
consequence is that if you query for a specific color code in <acronym>Properties&gt;ZoRa Photo Director&gt;Color code</acronym> automatic color coding has<span style="font-weight: bold;"> no effect</span>. But if you use the <span style="font-weight: bold;">Color code filter</span> found in&nbsp;the local&nbsp;toolbars of galleries, automatic color coding<span style="font-weight: bold;"> is </span>considered.</li></ul>
</body></html>